    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - May 13, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 💻 Google put Gemini where the cursor lives\n\nGoogle looked at the laptop and decided the missing feature was a chatbot hiding under the pointer. Restraint remains illegal.\n\n- **The hardware:** Google unveiled Googlebook, an Android-based laptop line built around Gemini, with Acer, Asus, Dell, HP and Lenovo lined up for first models this fall.\n- **The interface:** Google DeepMind detailed an AI-enabled pointer that can act on what users point at, from dates and images to PDFs and tables.\n- **The strategy:** this starts the long migration from cheap Chromebook utility to AI-native platform war with Microsoft.\n\n*The humble cursor has been promoted to junior agent. HR will be notified later.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/google-unveils-googlebooks-a-new-line-of-ai-native-laptops/) | [Google DeepMind](https://deepmind.google/blog/ai-pointer/)\n\n---\n\n## 🏦 Anthropic turned bank IT into a fire drill\n\nApparently the best way to modernize legacy banking systems is to point Mythos at them and watch everyone cancel lunch.\n\n- **The bank panic:** Reuters says large U.S. lenders are rushing to patch scores of weaknesses flagged by Anthropic's expensive Mythos tool, while warning smaller banks without access.\n- **The valuation fever:** Bloomberg Law reports Anthropic is in early talks to raise at least $30 billion at a valuation above $900 billion, barely months after a $380 billion round.\n- **The subtext:** frontier AI is now both the security scanner and the balance-sheet event.\n\n*Nothing says sober risk management like a trillion-dollar near-miss holding the vulnerability report.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via WHTC](https://whtc.com/2026/05/12/anthropics-mythos-sends-us-banks-rushing-to-plug-cyber-holes/) | [Bloomberg Law](https://news.bloomberglaw.com/artificial-intelligence/anthropic-in-talks-to-raise-30-billion-at-900-billion-value)\n\n---\n\n## 🧬 Isomorphic raised biotech money at AI speed\n\nDrug discovery has reached the stage where molecules need venture capital, cloud capacity and a very patient regulatory calendar.\n\n- **The round:** Isomorphic Labs announced $2.1 billion in Series B funding led by Thrive Capital, with Alphabet, GV, MGX, Temasek, CapitalG and the UK Sovereign AI Fund participating.\n- **The pitch:** the DeepMind spinout says the money will scale its AI drug design engine, expand globally and push drug candidates toward the clinic.\n- **The signal:** Reuters frames the raise as another bet that AlphaFold-style biology can become a pipeline, not just a demo.\n\n*AI drug discovery still has to meet biology, where the benchmarks are moody and the trials are expensive.*\n\n**Sources:** [Isomorphic Labs](https://www.isomorphiclabs.com/articles/isomorphic-labs-announces-series-b-investment-round) | [Reuters via Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/healthcare/articles/google-backed-isomorphic-raises-2-152155056.html)\n\n---\n\n## 🌊 Waymo discovered water is still undefeated\n\nThe robotaxi future is here, and it is learning the ancient human wisdom of not driving into floodwater.\n\n- **The recall:** NHTSA says Waymo is recalling 3,791 U.S. robotaxis using fifth- and sixth-generation automated driving systems.\n- **The bug:** TechCrunch says the vehicles could slow but fail to stop when facing flooded, untraversable lanes on higher-speed roads.\n- **The incident:** Waymo issued an interim software update after flooding problems in central Texas, including an empty robotaxi swept away in San Antonio.\n\n*Autonomy is hard. Hydrology, annoyingly, did not agree to the roadmap.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/05/12/waymo-issues-recall-to-deal-with-a-flooding-problem/) | [Reuters via KSL](https://www.ksl.com/article/51496327/waymo-recalls-3800-robotaxis-over-risk-of-entering-flooded-roads)\n\n---\n\n## 🧯 Samsung's AI chip boom found a union calendar\n\nThe memory market wanted uninterrupted HBM glory. The workers noticed the money first. Awkward timing for everyone with a data center spreadsheet.\n\n- **The breakdown:** Reuters says Samsung Electronics and its South Korean union failed to reach a pay deal on Wednesday.\n- **The threat:** the union says workers will strike for 18 days from May 21 if demands are not met.\n- **The stakes:** the dispute threatens production of AI and other chips at the world's largest memory maker, just as memory supply is already doing its usual shortage theater.\n\n*Turns out the AI supply chain includes people, and some of them can read margins.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via KELO](https://kelo.com/2026/05/12/samsung-elec-labour-union-fail-to-reach-pay-deal-as-strike-looms/) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/38e7a5030d3688850d3e8d8baf240f58)\n"
  }
]
